////Biceps Tendon - Pulley-lesion

Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 06 - Labrum & Ribbons of Shoulder MRI
And I select 'Biceps Tendon' from the Finding dropdown

When I select 'Pulley-lesion' radio button
Then 'Pulley-lesion type 1: isolated ligament lesion' radio button is enabled
And 'Pulley-lesion type 2: Rupture SSP ventral and articular' radio button is enabled
And 'Pulley-lesion type 3: Rupture SSC cranial and articular' radio button is enabled
And 'Pulley-lesion type 4: combination of Pulley 2 & 3' radio button is enabled

And 'Dislocation from sulcus' radio button is enabled
And 'Longitudinal splitting and dislocation into joint space' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Dislocation from sulcus' radio button
Then 'Medial' radio button is enabled
And 'Lateral' radio button is enabled
And 'Between the layers of the SSC' radio button is enabled
And 'Dorsal' radio button is enabled
